      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "844. Backspace String Compare\nEasy\nTopics\npremium lock icon\nCompanies\nGiven two strings s and t, return true if they are equal when\nboth are typed into empty text editors. '#' means a\nbackspace character.\n\nNote that after backspacing an empty text, the text will\ncontinue empty.\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nExample 1:\n\nac\nac\nInput: s = \"ab#c\", t = \"ad#c\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Both s and t become \"ac\".\nExample 2:\n\"\"\n\"\" -> true\n\nInput: s = \"ab##\", t = \"c#d#\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Both s and t become \"\".\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: s = \"a#c\", t = \"b\"\nOutput: false\nExplanation: s becomes \"c\" while t becomes \"b\".\n \n\nConstraints:\n\n1 <= s.length, t.length <= 200\ns and t only contain lowercase letters and '#' characters.\n \n\nFollow up: Can you solve it in O(n) time and O(1) space?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "844. Backspace String Compare\nEasy\nTopics\npremium lock icon\nCompanies\nGiven two strings s and t, return true if they are equal when both are typed into empty text editors. '#' means a backspace character.\n\nNote that after backspacing an empty text, the text will continue empty.\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nExample 1:\n\nac\nac\nInput: s = \"ab#c\", t = \"ad#c\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Both s and t become \"ac\".\nExample 2:\n\"\"\n\"\" -> true\n\nInput: s = \"ab##\", t = \"c#d#\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Both s and t become \"\".\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: s = \"a#c\", t = \"b\"\nOutput: false\nExplanation: s becomes \"c\" while t becomes \"b\".\n \n\nConstraints:\n\n1 <= s.length, t.length <= 200\ns and t only contain lowercase letters and '#' characters.\n \n\nFollow up: Can you solve it in O(n) time and O(1) space?",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
