      "text": "1. put all of them in a set\n2. make a character or variable and equate to #\n3. i will be checking the values  and then add the first letter, so if the # is not the first then,\ni move to the next letter, then after i check, i add it, so if the # is after a letter already in the\nset, i will remove the existing letter in the set",
